        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 20 at 7:54PM EDT by NWS Morristown TN</headline>
        <description>At 754 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Athens, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Madisonville, Fort Loudon State Park, Tariffville, Englewood, McGee
Carson Peninsula, Athens, Niota, Vonore, and Greenback.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 200 AM EDT for east
Tennessee.</instruction>
